The paper discusses deep generative models and regularization schemes for autoencoders, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of autoencoders for image generation suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), while the comparison with VAEs and the exploration of regularization techniques suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of density estimation also suggests a potential focus on natural language processing (cs.CL), while the use of neural networks suggests a potential focus on neural engineering (cs.NE).
